\begin_layout Section*
Word-pair Asymmetry
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This section reports on the asymmetry of the distribution of word-pairs.
 Some words appear more often at the beginning of sentences (and thus, appear
 more often on the left-hand-side of a word-pair) while others appear more
 often at the end (the period ending a sentence, treated as a word, is dominant
 on the right-hand side of pairs).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*
Left-right asymmetry - Definition
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Define the relation 
\begin_inset Formula $E(w_{1},w_{2})$
\end_inset

 as being the relation that both words 
\begin_inset Formula $w_{1}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $w_{2}$
\end_inset

 occur at the ends of an edge in the same sentence, but in arbitrary order.
 It is symmetric: 
\begin_inset Formula $E(w_{1},w_{2})=E(w_{2},w_{1})$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Given 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

 words, define the observation count of a relation 
\begin_inset Formula $R\left(w_{1},w_{2},\cdots,w_{n}\right)$
\end_inset

 between them as 
\begin_inset Formula $N\left(R,w_{1},w_{2},\cdots,w_{n}\right)$
\end_inset

.
 Use the symbol 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 to represent the ordered pair 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(w_{1},w_{2}\right)$
\end_inset

; that is, the relation is 
\begin_inset Formula $A\left(w_{1},w_{2}\right)$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
By these definitions, one has that 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
N(E,w_{1},w_{2})=N(A,w_{1},w_{2})+N(A,w_{2},w_{1})
\]

\end_inset

This is the symmetrized count.
 It is useful to mod out one of the two words, and to consider the sum
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
N(E,w)\equiv N(E,w,*)=\sum_{w_{2}}N(E,w,w_{2})
\]

\end_inset

This counts how often the word 
\begin_inset Formula $w$
\end_inset

 occurs at one end or the other of a word-pair.
 It is a distinct count from 
\begin_inset Formula $N(w)$
\end_inset

, which, by definition, counts only once per word in a sentence.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*
Left-right asymmetry - Results
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This section explores how often a given word occurs on the left side of
 a word pair, 
\emph on
vs.

\emph default
