\begin_layout Standard
Particularly interesting is the change in the support.
 The drop is dramatic: something like 5/6ths of the support disappears.
 This corresponds quite well with the earlier analysis: vectors with a large
 support correspond to effectively random pairings.
 Random pairings have a low MI.
